South African Corn Retreats, Tracking Decline in U.S. Benchmark

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-03-16T11:21:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/south-african-corn-retreats-tracking-decline-in-u-s-benchmark.html
Corn prices fell in  South Africa ,
tracking a decline in  Chicago .  White corn for July delivery, the most active contract on
the South African Futures Exchange, dropped 13 rand, or 0.8
percent, to close at 1,532 rand ($218) a metric ton in
Johannesburg. Meal made from the grain is the countryâ€™s staple
food.  Corn futures for May delivery fell by the 30-cents limit,
or 4.5 percent, to close at $6.36 a bushel on the Chicago Board
of Trade yesterday, on concern that the earthquake and nuclear
crisis in  Japan  will reduce demand for commodities.  In South Africa, yellow corn for July delivery declined 18
rand, or 1.1 percent, to 1,580 rand a ton. The country mainly
uses the grain as  animal feed .  Wheat for May delivery fell 31 rand, or 1 percent, to 2,964
rand a ton.  Gains or losses for the most active contracts of three
additional crops today were as follows. All prices are in rand
